===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Someone whose job is to speak for someone's case in a court of law; a [[counsel]]. {{defdate|from 14th c.}}
# Anyone who argues the case of another; an [[intercessor]]. {{defdate|from 14th c.}}
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Richard 3|text=I neuer did incense his Maiestie / Against the Duke of Clarence, but haue bin / An earnest '''aduocate''' to plead for him.}}
# A person who speaks in support of something, or someone. {{defdate|from 18th c.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1837|author={{w|Letitia Elizabeth Landon}}|title=Ethel Churchill|volume=1|page=104|text="I think," replied the young '''advocate''', unwilling to give up a point in which his feelings were interested, "that even you would believe in Walter Maynard's success in life, if you knew him. What has brought the world to its present state, but individual talent?"}}
#* '''2011''', Alix Lee, ''The Guardian'', 9 Oct 2011:
#*: He became a tireless '''advocate''' for the needs of adults with IMD throughout Britain and internationally.
# A person who supports others to make their voices heard, or ideally for them to speak up for themselves.
#: {{ux|en|Since she started working with her '''advocate''', she has become much more confident.}}

