===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To plead in favour of; to defend by argument, before a tribunal or the public; to support, vindicate, or recommend publicly.
#* '''7 March, 1624''', {{w|Robert Sanderson (theologian)|Robert Sanderson}}, ''sermon at the Assizes, at Lincoln''
#*: To '''advocate''' the cause of thy client.
#* '''16 June, 1784''', {{w|Edmund Burke}}, ''speech on reform of representation in the House of Commons''
#*: This is the only thing distinct and sensible, that has been '''advocated'''.
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[encourage]] [[support]] for something.
#: {{ux|en|I like trees, but I do not '''advocate''' living in them.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|year=1960|month=December|author=B. Perren|title=The role of the Great Central&mdash;present and future|journal=Trains Illustrated|page=765|text=Those who have '''advocated''' the closure of the G.C. have so far failed to say by which alternative route this North-to-West traffic could be carried.}}
#* {{quote-web|en|author=Alex McLevy|title=Westeros faces a disastrous final battle on the penultimate Game of Thrones (newbies)|url=https://tv.avclub.com/westeros-faces-its-final-battle-on-the-penultimate-game-1834706949|work={{w|The A.V. Club}}|date=12 May 2019|passage=Varys even leans on Jon to assume the Iron Throne, which means he very well knew he wasn’t going to be around much longer, if he’s openly '''advocating''' others commit treason as well.}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive|with ''for''}} To engage in advocacy.
#: {{ux|en|We have been '''advocating''' for changes in immigration law.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2020 June 3|author=Christian Wolmar|title=Unworkable policies cripple our beleaguered railway|journal=Rail|page=51|text=And why has no one in the [rail] industry '''advocated''' for a universal requirement for face covering (even if it's just a scarf or old tea towel), [...].}}
# {{lb|en|Scotland|law}} To [[appeal]] from an inferior [[court]] to the {{w|Court of Session}}.
# {{lb|en|Scotland|law|in higher courts}} To call a [[case]] before itself for [[decision]].

